SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 132
By Seal
A RESOLUTION to honor and commend the members and
coaches of the Mt. Horeb Hawks boys'
basketball team upon winning the Jefferson
County Elementary Basketball Tournament.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that this General Assembly should salute those student athletes
who, through their extraordinary efforts, have distinguished themselves as true champions of
whom we can all be proud; and
WHEREAS, one such exemplary group of lads is the Mt. Horeb Hawks boys' basketball
team, whose members have proven themselves to be the fiercest of competitors and truly
worthy of admiration by winning the Jefferson County Elementary Basketball Tournament, thus
completing a fairytale season; and
WHEREAS, the Hawks had flown high all season, but winning the tournament
championship capped their undefeated season with a trophy that placed a cherry atop their
perfect record; and
WHEREAS, in the championship tilt, the Hawks utilized their superior size to outmuscle
their opponent in the paint and easily defeated Jefferson County 42-26 to bring home the gold;
and
WHEREAS, the Hawks' superb performance would not have been possible without the
stellar leadership of Head Coach Whitney Felker and Assistant Coach Chastity Kiestler and the
unfailing support of their families, their fans, and their community; and
WHEREAS, the following lads were proud to soar across the sky as Hawks: Colton
Wice, Blaine Williams, Raylan Briggs, Bryce Kiestler, Nolan Frank, Eddie Yuen, Kylin Briggs,
Krueger Lawless, Cooper Benson, Whitley Ogle, Collin Hall, Karson Felker, and Atticus Miller;
and
